# Dependencies
node_modules/
# Third-party packages installed by npm in your future pracs. Large and rebuildable. Commiting it bloats the repo and causes merge pain.

# Logs
*.log
npm-debug.log*
# Runtime and crash logs. Useful locally only. Not source code. Regenerated on each run.

# Environment (safe to include even
.env
.env.*.local
# Environment variables: DB URI, secrets, ports. Must not be public.

# OS/editor
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
.vscode/
# .DS_Store
# macOS Finder metadata. Machine-specific clutter. Safe to ignore.
# Thumbs.db
# Windows Explorer cache. Machine-specific. Safe to ignore.
# .vscode/
# Editor settings and local extensions. Personal configuration. Avoids editor-specific noise.
